casebody.data:
Marv A. HUBBARD, Appellant,
v.
The STATE of Florida, Appellee. No. 3D18-555 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Third District. Opinion filed May 23, 2018. Marv A. Hubbard, in proper person. Pamela Jo Bondi, Attorney General, for appellee. Before SUAREZ, SALTER, and FERNANDEZ, JJ. PER CURIAM.

Defendant filed this appeal of the trial court's denial of his petition for writ of Habeas Corpus. As the trial court correctly noted, the petition is actually a motion to vacate judgment, which was denied by the trial court. We treat the petition the same and affirm the trial court's denial.

Affirmed.
